PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F337A1781621296
OL,3,CFormer Labour deputy leader Roy
OL,4,CHattersley dies, aged 93
OL,6,FKnown as Labour's "nearly man," he
OL,7,Ffailed to gain the leadership of the
OL,8,Fparty he loved and spent more than two
OL,9,Fdecades of his 33 years as an MP on
OL,10,Fthe opposition benches.
OL,12,FPrime Minister Sir Keir wrote on X:
OL,13,F"Roy Hattersley was a giant of the
OL,14,FLabour movement.
OL,16,F"Through decades of service, including
OL,17,Fas deputy leader and a minister, he
OL,18,Fnever lost his belief in a more equal
OL,19,FBritain.
OL,26,@nD@SOUnD@_O]uD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/11
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,338,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F337A1781621296
OL,3,CFormer Labour deputy leader Roy
OL,4,CHattersley dies, aged 93
OL,6,F"My thoughts are with his wife Maggie
OL,7,Fand his family."
OL,9,FLord Kinnock, who led the party from
OL,10,F1983 to 1992, said: "I am deeply
OL,11,Fsaddened to hear that Roy has died and
OL,12,Fsend my profound sympathy to Maggie.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@PO]rD@UOU
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/11
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,338,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F337A1781621296
OL,3,CFormer Labour deputy leader Roy
OL,4,CHattersley dies, aged 93
OL,6,F"Roy was a socialist of deep
OL,7,Fconviction, a dedicated democrat who
OL,8,Fbelieved that liberty should be
OL,9,Funqualified by anything but
OL,10,Fresponsibility and never by background
OL,11,For fortune. He held that freedom had
OL,12,Fto be made real and secure by
OL,13,Fcollective action and contribution, by
OL,14,Faccountability, and by equality.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/11
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,338,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F337A1781621296
OL,3,CFormer Labour deputy leader Roy
OL,4,CHattersley dies, aged 93
OL,6,F"He was fluent and courageous in
OL,7,Fexpressing these beliefs in speech and
OL,8,Fwriting and wrote countless columns
OL,9,Fand published 20 books. He was never
OL,10,Fsolemn nor deferential and his common
OL,11,Fsense, humour and endless stories made
OL,12,Fhim excellent company.
OL,14,F"All of this made him a valued comrade
OL,15,Fand an incomparable asset to the
OL,16,FLabour Party, to British democracy and
OL,17,Fto wider humanity."
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOUyD@SO]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/11
