PN,33708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F337A1781621296
OL,3,CFormer Labour deputy leader Roy
OL,4,CHattersley dies, aged 93
OL,6,FTory former Commons deputy speaker
OL,7,FNigel Evans wrote: "Roy Hattersley was
OL,8,Fone of the genuine old Labour
OL,9,Fpoliticians ` fiercely academic with
OL,10,Fhis true roots in support of working
OL,11,Fpeople ` I was lucky enough to cross
OL,12,Fhis last term in the Commons.
OL,14,F"It's people like Roy that shaped
OL,15,Fpolitics for a generation with
OL,16,Fabsolute belief in improving the lot
OL,17,Fof the people he represented..... on
OL,18,Fthe lighter side he was a gift to
OL,19,Fspitting image ` but his legacy was
OL,20,Fnot that of his caricature.
OL,26,@oD@TOUvD@AOU
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G8/11
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,338,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F337A1781621296
OL,3,CFormer Labour deputy leader Roy
OL,4,CHattersley dies, aged 93
OL,6,F"I pay tribute to the passing of a
OL,7,Fwarrior of a politics more real."
OL,9,FMr Hattersley spent much of the
OL,10,Fparty's wilderness years of the 1980s
OL,11,Fbattling to keep it together just as
OL,12,Fideological infighting threatened to
OL,13,Ftear it apart.
OL,15,FHe was credited with helping to steer
OL,16,Fthe party away from the policies which
OL,17,Fhad made it unelectable in the eyes of
OL,18,Fmany voters ` including its support
OL,19,Ffor unilateral nuclear disarmament and
OL,20,Fits opposition to the European
OL,21,FCommunity.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@aO]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G9/11
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,338,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F337A1781621296
OL,3,CFormer Labour deputy leader Roy
OL,4,CHattersley dies, aged 93
OL,6,FBut when Tony Blair, who had once
OL,7,Fworked for him, finally succeeded in
OL,8,Fregaining No 10 for Labour, he became
OL,9,Fone of his most outspoken critics,
OL,10,Faccusing him of abandoning its
OL,11,Fsocialist principles.
OL,13,FAs a passionate advocate for the
OL,14,Fcauses of redistribution and equality,
OL,15,Fparticularly in the education system,
OL,16,Fhe was dismayed by New Labour's
OL,17,Fwholesale embrace of the market
OL,18,Feconomy.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G10/11
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
